# 🚀 Day 44/90 – Designing the Complete User Journey (User Flow)

Welcome to **Day 44!** 🎉

From today onwards, we're no longer learning generic software engineering concepts.

We're going to **build your actual Blood Report Analyzer app**, one decision at a time.

Today we'll answer:

> **"What exactly happens from the moment a user installs the app until they understand their blood report?"**

This is called the **User Journey** or **User Flow**.

---

# 🎯 Today's Goal

By the end of today, you'll have the complete workflow of your app.

This will become the blueprint for development.

---

# Step 1 – User Downloads the App

The user opens Google Play Store.

↓

Searches

**Blood Report Analyzer**

↓

Installs the app.

↓

Opens it for the first time.

---

# Step 2 – Welcome Screen

The app should introduce itself.

Example:

```
Welcome to Blood Report Analyzer

Understand your blood reports
in simple language.

Track your health over time.

Compare reports.

Powered by AI.

[ Get Started ]
```

Simple.

No clutter.

---

# Step 3 – Sign Up

New users create an account.

Information:

* Name
* Email
* Password

↓

Create Account

↓

Verify Email

↓

Account Ready

---

# Step 4 – Login

Returning users simply enter:

* Email
* Password

↓

Home Screen

---

# Step 5 – Home Screen

This is the first screen users see.

It should have only the important actions.

```
Hello, Srujan 👋

Upload Report

Recent Reports

Health Trends

Profile
```

No unnecessary buttons.

---

# Step 6 – Upload Report

User taps

**Upload Report**

Choose:

📄 PDF

or

📷 Camera

or

🖼 Gallery

↓

Upload

---

# Step 7 – OCR Processing

After upload,

show a progress screen.

```
Uploading...

Extracting blood values...

Please wait...
```

Usually 5–15 seconds depending on the report.

---

# Step 8 – Review Extracted Values

This is one of the most important screens.

The app should display:

```
Hemoglobin

13.2

✏ Edit

----------------

HbA1c

5.8

✏ Edit

----------------

Vitamin D

18

✏ Edit
```

The user can correct OCR mistakes.

Only after confirmation do we continue.

---

# Step 9 – AI Analysis

Now the backend sends the confirmed values to AI.

AI generates:

```
Summary

Hemoglobin appears within
the reference range shown on
your report.

Vitamin D is below the
reference range.

HbA1c is within the normal
range.
```

Keep the language simple and understandable.

---

# Step 10 – Save Report

Everything is saved.

* PDF
* Blood values
* AI summary
* Upload date

Nothing is overwritten.

Every upload becomes part of the user's history.

---

# Step 11 – Report History

The user taps:

History

Example:

```
July 2026

Apollo Hospital

----------------

April 2026

Vijaya Diagnostics

----------------

January 2026

Thyrocare
```

Newest reports should appear first.

---

# Step 12 – Open a Report

User taps:

July Report

The app displays:

* Original PDF
* Blood values
* AI explanation
* Upload date
* Hospital name

Everything on one screen.

---

# Step 13 – Compare Reports

The user selects:

January

↓

July

The app shows:

| Test       | January | July | Trend      |
| ---------- | ------- | ---- | ---------- |
| Hemoglobin | 11.8    | 13.2 | ⬆ Improved |
| HbA1c      | 6.5     | 5.8  | ⬇ Improved |
| Vitamin D  | 18      | 28   | ⬆ Improved |

This is one of the biggest value propositions of your app.

---

# Step 14 – Health Trends

Instead of just tables,

show graphs.

Example:

```
Hemoglobin

11.8

↓

12.5

↓

13.2
```

Users understand trends much faster visually.

---

# Step 15 – Profile

The profile page should be simple.

```
Name

Email

Password

Logout
```

Nothing more is needed for the MVP.

---

# Complete User Journey

```
Install App

↓

Sign Up

↓

Login

↓

Home

↓

Upload Report

↓

OCR

↓

Review OCR

↓

AI Analysis

↓

Save Report

↓

History

↓

Compare Reports

↓

Health Trends
```

This is the complete journey of your first version.

---

# Features We Will NOT Build in MVP

To launch faster, we'll postpone:

❌ Doctor appointments

❌ Medicine reminders

❌ Fitness tracking

❌ Diet planning

❌ Smartwatch integration

❌ Family sharing

❌ Chat with doctors

❌ Insurance integration

These can become Version 2 or Version 3.

